-- Spurs Top Grizzlies 93-89 in Overtime for 2-0 NBA Playoffs Lead
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-05-22T04:56:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-22/spurs-top-grizzlies-93-89-in-overtime-for-2-0-nba-playoffs-lead.html
Tim Duncan  scored six of his 17
points in overtime and the San Antonio Spurs won 93-89 after
blowing a 13-point fourth-quarter lead to take a two-games-to-none lead in their National Basketball Association playoff
series against the Memphis Grizzlies.  In tonight’s game, the defending champion Miami Heat host
the Indiana Pacers in the first game of the best-of-seven
Eastern Conference finals.  Tony Parker  added 15 points and 18 assists, his career high
in the postseason, for the Spurs -- who held an 18-point lead in
the third quarter and were ahead 83-70 with seven minutes, 22
seconds left in the fourth period.  “We knew they were going to fight,” Duncan said in a
televised interview. “I was glad I was able to play in
overtime.”  The Grizzlies trailed 46-31 at the half before outscoring
the Spurs 33-30 in the third quarter. Memphis then scored 21
points while holding San Antonio to nine points in the final
period, using a 15-2 run to tie the game 85-85 and force the
overtime at AT&T Center in San Antonio.  “We just have to keep fighting,” Grizzlies coach Lionel Hollins said. “We have to make our own breaks. We have to go
home and take care of business.”  The Grizzlies host Game 3 on May 25.  Mike Conley  and Jerryd Bayless each scored 18 points,  Zach Randolph  had 15 points and 18 rebounds and  Marc Gasol 
contributed 12 points and 14 rebounds for the Grizzlies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
